<HL>
   B.F. Goodrich Co. Expansion
</HL>
<DATE>
05/01/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   GR
</CO>
<LP>
   AKRON, Ohio -- B.F. Goodrich Co. said it will invest about
$14 million to expand capacity to produce hydrophilic resins
at Calvert City, Ky., and Pohang, South Korea.
   The expansion, which is scheduled to be completed in
mid-1991, will increase the company's world-wide capacity for
the materials by 35%, Goodrich said.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Hydrophilic resins are additives used as thickening and
suspension agents in cosmetics and personal-care products,
and a number of other uses, the company said.
   Goodrich is a plastics, specialty chemicals and aerospace
products concern.
</TEXT>
